data.metadata: {"description":"I‚Äôve known Pavil through the Pudgy/Abstract community since early 2024. What sets him apart is not only his style but his process. He starts with a short brief, quickly sends pencil sketches, agrees on a color palette, and then executes cleanly either on stream or offline.\nI first noticed him during live graffiti sessions on the Abstract portal: he turned multiple PFPs into cohesive, wall-ready compositions instead of just copying avatars. Later, at a local Pudgy meetup, he handled a live painting segment with clear preparation, no delays, and strong composition, and attendees ended up using the artwork as social headers.\nHis contribution to the community is real: he regularly supports Pudgy Russia, helps creators with custom pieces, and communicates professionally (fast replies, realistic timelines, no drama). If you need someone who delivers striking graffiti and represents the culture responsibly, Pavil is reliable and easy to recommend."}

translation.translatedDescription:
I‚Äôve known Pavil through the Pudgy/Abstract community since early 2024. What sets him apart is not only his style but his process. He starts with a short brief, quickly sends pencil sketches, agrees on a color palette, and then executes cleanly either on stream or offline.
I first noticed him during live graffiti sessions on the Abstract portal: he turned multiple PFPs into cohesive, wall-ready compositions instead of just copying avatars. Later, at a local Pudgy meetup, he handled a live painting segment with clear preparation, no delays, and strong composition, and attendees ended up using the artwork as social headers.
His contribution to the community is real: he regularly supports Pudgy Russia, helps creators with custom pieces, and communicates professionally (fast replies, realistic timelines, no drama). If you need someone who delivers striking graffiti and represents the culture responsibly, Pavil is reliable and easy to recommend.

translation.translatedDescription:
I discovered PAVIL through his art, and it was a true revelation.
His talent is incredible: the frescoes he creates are of a richness and precision that leave you speechless. Each detail tells a story, each color is chosen with care, and the whole exudes a rare emotion.

But what makes PAVIL even more admirable is his personality. Beyond his immense talent, he is someone warm, humble, and kind, always ready to share his passion and encourage others. Working or interacting with him is a real pleasure.

Discovering his work is much more than admiring art: it is feeling the passion and energy he puts into each of his creations.

data.metadata: {"description":"I have been following Skarly since 2024 and joined OCH as one of the earliest participants, and during this time I have seen him methodically turn an idea into a product while keeping a high standard. He is a rare kind of builder who does the work himself, engages with the community, explains decisions clearly, and iterates quickly. Most importantly he does everything with heart, and you can feel it in the details of the game design and onchain logic. OCH feels cohesive and genuinely excellent, a product you want to return to, which is why it keeps gaining more fans. I like everything Skarly is doing and I am confident he will continue to raise the bar for onchain gaming."}

translation.translatedDescription: I have been following Skarly since 2024 and joined OCH as one of the earliest participants, and during this time I have seen him methodically turn an idea into a product while keeping a high standard. He is a rare kind of builder who does the work himself, engages with the community, explains decisions clearly, and iterates quickly. Most importantly he does everything with heart, and you can feel it in the details of the game design and onchain logic. OCH feels cohesive and genuinely excellent, a product you want to return to, which is why it keeps gaining more fans. I like everything Skarly is doing and I am confident he will continue to raise the bar for onchain gaming.
